  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6787 sitting just below the massive 6800 gamma wall (7.0B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher as they're long gamma and need to hedge by selling rallies. The PIN regime combined with the recent wall break and GEX surge suggests dealers will provide strong resistance at 6800 and create a magnetic pull toward the 6775-6750 zone where gamma remains heavy. Key levels: watch 6800 as the primary resistance where dealer selling intensifies, and 6680 GEX flip as the critical support—any break below flips dealers short gamma and triggers accelerated selling.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect mean reversion lower with 6800 acting as a brick wall.",
